  @{fg shine}TAFrame@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TAFrames@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TAHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}TAMaxWidth@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}TAMillis@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TANoAnim@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}TANoLoop@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}TAObjHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}TAObjWidth@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}TAPrecision@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}TASelectedFrame@{fg text}
  S IS

  @{fg shine}TAStartFrame@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TAWidth@{fg text}
  N IGN

  @{fg shine}TAViewMode@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Normal
     o Scale
     o Repeat

  All the G attribute are readable only after the window the
  TransferAnim object belongs to is opened. Really don't know if
  it is a TransferAnim.mcc feature, bug or a TransferAnim.rxmec
  bug.

  TAFile is defined as S, but setting its value seems to not work
  at all. So you must delete the TransferAnim object and recreate
  it, if you want to change the current file.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

